body:
I have these functions in `file_1.sv`

```sv
  bit [7 :0] y_mem  [0:1000-1];
  int addr_8;
  logic signed [3:0][7:0] data_8;

  export "DPI-C" function write_y;
  export "DPI-C" function read_y;

  function void write_y (input longint addr, input int data);
    data_8 = data;
    for (int i=0; i<4; i++) 
      y_mem[addr + i] = data_8[i];
  endfunction

  function int read_y (input longint addr);
    for (int i=0; i<4; i++) 
      data_8[i] = y_mem[addr + i];
    read_y = data_8;
  endfunction
```

In `file2.c`, I import them as:
```c
extern "C" void write_y (int * addr, int data);
extern "C" int  read_y  (int * addr);
```

And I get the error:
```
%Error: unknown:0: Testbench C called 'write_y' but scope wasn't set, perhaps due to dpi import call without 'context', or missing svSetScope. See IEEE 1800-2017 35.5.3.
```


I tried setting the scope:
```
svSetScope (svGetScopeFromName ("file_1.sv"));
```

and I get the error:
```
../../c/file2.c:15:13: error: expected constructor, destructor, or type conversion before ‘(’ token
   15 |   svSetScope(svGetScopeFromName("file_1.sv"));
      |             ^
```

I tried changing the function to task, same error. 

How do I correctly export an SV function/task?
